My Conversations

  • MuddyMole
    Xper 7 Age 40 , mho 46%
    Follow 6 h
    Report

    Stop going on about it?
    The "LGB" part is settled. All but the most extreme religious nuts are fine with it, and noone goes on about it any more.
    It's only the trans, non-binary, etc parts that are controversial, and it's actually the *conservatives* who are the ones going on and on about it, trying to keep it in the public spotlight, because they see it as a political weakness. It forces liberals to speak out in defence of those people, which they otherwise wouldn't do, because they know it will cost them the votes of "moderates".

    I'm sad to say it, but if the conservatives didn't keep banging on about it, the liberals would happily keep quiet about it too - and you'd be fine, because trans/non-binary people make up such a tiny fraction of the population that you'll probably never even meet one, let alone have their behaviour impact you in any way whatsoever.

    It's similar to the issue of abortion bans. The reason Lindsey Graham got so much stick from other conservatives when he introduced a potential federal abortion ban, is that it kept people talking about the issue, when conservatives would much rather talk about something else, since they know their stance is wildly unpopular with voters.
